Styx environment
----------------

run `sudo ./bootstrap` from the project's root directory in order to setup your
production environment, or instead similarly run 'sudo ./dev.[ARCH]' in order to
set up a development environment.

once bootstrapped, activate your environment with '. styx/bin/activate' or
'. styx-dev/bin/activate' as appropriate.


root folder 
-----------

cerberus/
	cerberus server - handles all incoming api requests from the outside world

gaia/
	gaia server - server placeholder

hermes/
	hermes server - serves the admin interface to processors

fcgi/
	contains the FastCGI scripts hosting cerberus, gaia and hermes through a flup FastCGI WSGI server
lib/
	the manhattan library: implements everything from db access to processor and bank interfaces

nginx/
	nginx configuration scripts

styx/
styx-dev/
	virtualenv environments are stored in these respective folders

upstart/
	upstart scripts for the fcgi servers

bootstrap
dev.[ARCH]
	bootstrap scripts for fetching required resources. bootstrap is written for solely for ubuntu.

cerberus.py
gaia.py
hermes.py
	development helper scripts for launching the servers using flask in development mode (as opposed to fcgi)
